subSubSection.paragraph:
Female genitalia.
Cornu broad, comparatively short, slightly curved (
Figure 31
), bursa sclerites large, usually with five strong spines (
Figure 30
).

Male genitalia.
Median lobe slender, round in cross-section, straight, slightly narrowed in the middle (
Figure 32A
), apex strongly carinate ventrally (
Figure 32B
). Tectum long, broad, incised apically. Endophallic spiculae slender, ventral and dorsal pair short and straight, middle pair much longer, curved inwards. Orifice very small, circular, with shallow insicion.
